premise_source_doc_sentence: Charles is a masculine given name from the French form Charles of a Germanic name Karl .
The original Anglo-Saxon was Ċearl or Ċeorl , as the name of King Cearl of Mercia , that disappeared after the Norman conquest of England .
The corresponding Old Norse form is Karl , and the German form is also Karl .
